        <div class="stat-value">40.6%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Conversion Rate</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="privacy-container">
    <section class="welcome">
      <h2>Welcome to Data Privacy Hub</h2>
      <p>This platform explores the challenges, laws, and solutions for protecting student data in educational systems.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Understand your rights under privacy regulations.</li>
        <li>Learn about common data privacy issues in education.</li>
        <li>Discover best practices for safeguarding information.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="features-section">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>Data Protection Laws</h3>
        <p>Explore various data protection regulations like GDPR, CCPA, and FERPA that govern how personal information should be handled.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>Privacy Issues</h3>
        <p>Understand the common privacy challenges faced by educational institutions and how they impact students and faculty.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>Best Practices</h3>
        <p>Learn about effective strategies and solutions for maintaining data privacy in educational environments.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="highlight">
      <div class="definition-box">
        <h3>What is Data Privacy?</h3>
        <p>Data privacy refers to the proper handling, processing, storage, and protection of personal information collected by organizations. It focuses on how data should be collected, stored, managed, and shared with third parties while complying with legal requirements and respecting individual rights.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-box">
        <p>"Protecting student data is not just a legal obligation, it is a moral responsibility of educational institutions."</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

